critique: This document is an executive order from 1939 that corrects the description of the Waianae-Kai Military Reservation in Hawaii. It involves surveying inaccuracies and extending a road right-of-way. Given the historical context and the nature of the document, it doesn't directly address modern political issues. Therefore, most axes should be neutral. The document centralizes control by modifying federal land for military purposes, which suggests a slight increase in federal power.
